Breach of contract of the said defendant in failing to pay the plaintiffs as co- partners as aforesaid the sum two hundred and fourteen dollars and seventy one cents ($214.71) due the plaintiffs as copartners as aforesaid for goods sold and delivered by the plaintiffs as copartners as aforesaid to the said defendants at diverse times between the first day of October 1884, and the sixth day of December, 1884, both inclusive, at Tacoma in said county, at the agree price in the aggregate of two hundred and fourteen dollars & seventy one cents, no part whereof has been paid;
1277
that the said defendant is indebted to the plaintiffs as copartners as aforesaid in said cause of action to the plain in the said sum of $214.71 with interest thereon from the sixth day of December 1884, one and above all set offs and counterclaims,, and that the said indebtedness is not sicined either in whole or in part, by any mortgages or lier upon any real or personal property, or any pledge of personal property; and that an action has been commenced in said Court in said cause of action by the filing of a complaint with the Clerk and the issuing of a summons and certified copy of said complaint
